######

Total points: 100

Please extend the code in lectures/lecture-06-09/lambda3.py
to handle the following language constructs and operators:

| DElist_nil of () // HX: for nil-list
| DElist_cons of (dexp, dexp) // for cons-list

Please support the following operators (as OP1s)
1. list_nilq (testing if a list is nil)
2. list_head (returning the head of a non-nil list)
3. list_tail (returning the tail of a non-nil list)

In particular, you need to produce a running version
of [dexp_evalenv] that can handle the evaluation of lists.

