Total points: 20+20=40

Please TRANSLATE the following function into LAMBDA:

(*

The following ones are implemented as OP1s:

def fnlist_nilq(xs):
    return (xs.ctag == "nil")
def fnlist_head(xs):
    assert (xs.ctag == "cons")
    return xs.arg1
def fnlist_tail(xs):
    assert (xs.ctag == "cons")
    return xs.arg2

HX-2026-06-10:
[fnlist_nilq] is implemented as OP1
(that is, operator with one argument). Also,
[fnlist_head] and [fnlist_tail] are implemented as OP1s.

*)

The following two functions need to be translated
into LAMBDA (dexp):

def fnlist_tally(xs):
  if fnlist_nilq(xs):
    return 0
  else:
    return fnlist_hd(xs) + fnlist_tally(fnlist_tl(arg2))

def fnlist_range1(n):
  def loop(i, res):
    if i >= n:
      return res
    else:
      return loop(i+1, fnlist_cons(n-1-i, res))
  return loop(0, fnlist_nil())

Your translation should be correctly interpreted by
[dexp_eval000].

